<key id="d4" for="node" attr.name="file_path" attr.type="string"/>
<key id="d3" for="node" attr.name="source_id" attr.type="string"/>
<key id="d2" for="node" attr.name="description" attr.type="string"/>
<key id="d1" for="node" attr.name="entity_type" attr.type="string"/>
<key id="d0" for="node" attr.name="entity_id" attr.type="string"/>
<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Government">
  <data key="d0">Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Government is the contracting authority that issues orders, exercises options to extend services or contract terms, evaluates offers, and allots funding for incrementally funded items.&lt;SEP&gt;Government is the entity entering into the contract, estimating costs, and receiving compensation through liquidated damages for nonperformance.&lt;SEP&gt;The Government owns and controls historical resources, provides facilities for contract use, inspects performance, and assesses remedies for contractor failures.&lt;SEP&gt;Government conducts price analysis, evaluates proposals for unbalanced pricing and inconsistencies, and determines acceptability based on risks and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor">
  <data key="d0">Contractor</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contractor performs services, completes orders, rerepresents small business status, certifies indirect costs, and complies with evaluation preferences and joint venture requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;Contractor is the entity responsible for performing services, subject to liquidated damages for delays or unsatisfactory performance, and complying with incorporated clauses.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contractor is responsible for performing contract requirements, including protecting resources, registering with FedMall, providing identifications, and facing consequences for non-performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Contracting Officer">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Contracting Officer specifies time limits for negotiating subcontracting plans and determines eligibility for contract award.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer exercises options by written notice, requires rerepresentations for orders, establishes unilateral indirect cost rates if needed, and provides full text of referenced clauses upon request.&lt;SEP&gt;The Contracting Officer directs work resumption after discoveries, receives notifications, and holds authority to bind the Government in contract matters.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting Officer is the official who deems appropriate methodologies for price analysis consistent with FAR 15.404-1.&lt;SEP&gt;Contracting Officer is the government representative who determines the time for the pre-performance conference and discusses scheduling and work administration with the contractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Secretary of Labor">
  <data key="d0">Secretary of Labor</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Secretary of Labor provides prevailing labor rates used for adjusting rates in service extension options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Administration">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Administration</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Small Business Administration determines affiliation, maintains the List of Qualified HUBZone Small Business Concerns, and sets size standards based on NAICS codes.&lt;SEP&gt;Small Business Administration approves Mentor-Protege Agreements that provide exceptions for joint venture experience submissions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A HUBZone small business concern qualifies for a 10 percent price evaluation preference unless waived, must perform at least 40 percent of joint venture work beyond administrative functions, and requires rerepresentation of status.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Concern">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Concern</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A small business concern is independently owned, not dominant in its field, qualified under 13 CFR part 121 size standards, and includes categories like women-owned or veteran-owned for set-asides and rerepresentations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Option to Extend Services">
  <data key="d0">Option to Extend Services</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.217-8 allows the Government to require continued performance of services up to 6 months total, with rates adjustable based on prevailing labor rates, exercised by written notice prior to expiration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Option to Extend the Term of the Contract">
  <data key="d0">Option to Extend the Term of the Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.217-9 enables the Government to extend the contract term up to 96 months total with preliminary notice at least 30 days before expiration and formal written notice prior to completion of the current period.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns">
  <data key="d0">Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.219-4 adds a 10 percent factor to non-HUBZone offers for evaluation, applies the preference on a line item basis after other factors, and favors HUBZone concerns in tied evaluations with large businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation">
  <data key="d0">Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.219-28 requires the Contractor to rerepresent size and socioeconomic status within specified timeframes after novations, mergers, or for long-term contracts and orders, using SAM or a certification form.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires">
  <data key="d0">Statement of Equivalent Rates for Federal Hires</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.222-42 identifies employee classes like Boiler Tender and Electrician with equivalent monetary wages and fringe benefits for federal hires under the Service Contract Labor Standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Certification of Final Indirect Costs">
  <data key="d0">Certification of Final Indirect Costs</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.242-4 mandates the Contractor to certify proposals for final indirect cost rates using a specified format signed by a vice president or chief financial officer, with failure leading to unilateral rates by the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Clauses Incorporated by Reference">
  <data key="d0">Clauses Incorporated by Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.252-2 incorporates other clauses by reference with the same force as full text, accessible electronically at specified URLs including acquisition.gov and farsite.hill.af.mil.&lt;SEP&gt;This clause states that the contract incorporates one or more clauses by reference with the same force and effect as if given in full text, and the full text is available upon request or electronically at specified addresses including https://acquisition.gov/browse/index/far, http://farsite.hill.af.mil/vmdfara.htm, and http://www.secnav.navy.mil/rda/Pages/NMCARS.aspx.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Alterations in Contract">
  <data key="d0">Alterations in Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.252-4 specifies alterations to portions of the contract as indicated.&lt;SEP&gt;This clause indicates that portions of the contract are altered as specified in the blank provided.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Authorized Deviations in Clauses">
  <data key="d0">Authorized Deviations in Clauses</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Clause 52.252-6 marks clauses with authorized deviations by adding "(DEVIATION)" after the date or regulation name for FAR and DFARS.&lt;SEP&gt;This clause explains that the use of any Federal Acquisition Regulation clause with an authorized deviation is indicated by adding "(DEVIATION)" after the date, and similarly for Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Limitation of Government's Obligation">
  <data key="d0">Limitation of Government's Obligation</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS Clause 252.232-7007 applies to incrementally funded contract line items, allots initial funding amounts specified on task orders, and limits performance to available funds.&lt;SEP&gt;This clause addresses incrementally funded contract line items, specifying available funds, contractor performance limits, notification requirements at 85 percent funding, equitable adjustments, and an allotment schedule detailed in paragraph (j), with provisions for termination and disputes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Acquisition Regulation">
  <data key="d0">Federal Acquisition Regulation</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal Acquisition Regulation defines service contracts under 37.101 and includes clauses such as 52.222-43 and 52.222-32 for wage adjustments in option periods.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Acquisition Regulation (FAR) provides cost principles applicable to indirect costs, clauses like 52.217-8, and governs evaluation preferences and small business rerepresentations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Federal Acquisition Regulation is referenced as 48 CFR Chapter 1, with clauses incorporated by reference and deviations indicated.&lt;SEP&gt;Federal Acquisition Regulation provides the framework for FAR clauses incorporated by reference in Section K, covering representations on telecommunications, responsibility matters, arms control, and foreign procurements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="System for Award Management">
  <data key="d0">System for Award Management</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">The System for Award Management (SAM) is used by the Contractor to validate or update representations and certifications for small business status.&lt;SEP&gt;The System for Award Management (SAM) is referenced for representations and certifications under FAR 52.204-7.&lt;SEP&gt;System for Award Management is the online registration system where offerors complete and maintain representations and certifications applicable to the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;This is the entity operating the website https://sam.gov/ where Section J attachments are posted with the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9e005e41da996ebb18d009a4f87b0e3c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="North American Industry Classification System">
  <data key="d0">North American Industry Classification System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The North American Industry Classification System (NAICS) assigns codes to the contract for applying small business size standards, such as 561210 with a $47,000,000 limit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Long-term Contract">
  <data key="d0">Long-term Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A long-term contract exceeds five years in duration, including options, but excludes extensions up to six months under clauses like 52.217-8.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS">
  <data key="d0">DFARS</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS is the Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement, with clauses incorporated by reference into the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Federal Acquisition Supplement (DFARS) governs clauses with authorized deviations, indicated by "(DEVIATION)" after the regulation name.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Task Order">
  <data key="d0">Task Order</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Task orders specify funding allotments, completion dates, and performance requirements for incrementally funded contract line items and services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Joint Venture">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Joint Venture</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A HUBZone joint venture requires at least 40 percent of the aggregate work to be performed by HUBZone small business parties, exceeding administrative functions, and complies with 13 CFR part 126.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I">
  <data key="d0">Postaward Small Business Program Rerepresentation Alternate I</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Alternate I of clause 52.219-28 substitutes paragraph (h)(1) to require the Contractor to represent small business size status for each NAICS code assigned to the contract, such as 561210 with a $47,000,000 standard.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Woman-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Woman-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Woman-Owned Small Business is targeted at 9% of planned subcontract dollars.&lt;SEP&gt;A woman-owned small business concern qualifies for set-asides and rerepresentation under socioeconomic categories, including joint ventures compliant with 13 CFR 127.506.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Service-Disabled Veteran-Owned Small Business has a 5% target in the subcontracting plan.&lt;SEP&gt;A service-disabled veteran-owned small business concern is eligible for set-asides, joint ventures under 13 CFR 128.402, and requires rerepresentation of status.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Economically Disadvantaged Women-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Economically Disadvantaged Women-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">An economically disadvantaged women-owned small business concern qualifies for specific set-asides and joint ventures per 13 CFR 127.506.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Veteran-Owned Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Veteran-Owned Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A veteran-owned small business concern includes service-disabled variants and requires rerepresentation for contract awards and orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Disadvantaged Business">
  <data key="d0">Small Disadvantaged Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Small Disadvantaged Business is targeted at 5% in NAVFAC's subcontracting goals.&lt;SEP&gt;A small disadvantaged business concern is defined under 13 CFR 124.1001 and qualifies for socioeconomic preferences and rerepresentations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Novation Agreement">
  <data key="d0">Novation Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">A novation agreement transfers contract rights and obligations, triggering rerepresentation of small business status within 30 days after execution or contract modification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Service Contract Labor Standards">
  <data key="d0">Service Contract Labor Standards</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">The Service Contract Labor Standards statute, under 29 CFR Part 4, requires identification of employee classes and equivalent wages for federal hires in service contracts.&lt;SEP&gt;Service Contract Labor Standards, formerly the Service Contract Act of 1965, governs wage and fringe benefit rates for covered employees, with no escalation in recurring work prices for option periods per FAR 52.222-43.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="13 CFR Part 121">
  <data key="d0">13 CFR Part 121</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">13 CFR Part 121 provides criteria and size standards for qualifying small business concerns, including NAICS-based determinations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Supply Schedule Contract">
  <data key="d0">Federal Supply Schedule Contract</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">A Federal Supply Schedule contract under subpart 8.4 issues orders that may require rerepresentation except for certain set-asides.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790152</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003 is the identifier for a performance-based contract providing Base Operations Support services at specified naval facilities.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation number associated with the contract details in Section F.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is a government contract document that includes sections on contract clauses, liquidated damages provisions, and various FAR and DFARS clauses incorporated by reference or full text.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the identifier for the solicitation incorporating evaluation preferences and various clauses for small business concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation number for the acquisition involving base operations support services.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation and contract identifier referenced throughout the document sections.&lt;SEP&gt;N6945025R0003 is the solicitation identifier for the RFP, referenced in attachment file names and page footers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-96e30762ee04dbe2af303802d3d2a936&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bafeb026eba657c5147474a89dc0e6f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb</data>
