<node id="NAVFAC Maximo">
  <data key="d0">NAVFAC Maximo</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">A data system critical for government planning, requiring maintenance of service provider, asset, specification, and characteristic meter reading data fields.&lt;SEP&gt;This asset management system is referenced in reporting procedures, naming conventions, and acronyms in Section J attachments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="USMCmax">
  <data key="d0">USMCmax</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">This system has standard asset data load templates and user guides provided in Section J attachments.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="City of Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">City of Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">This city is associated with the Pump Station Inspection Form in J-0200000-07 Forms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="31 U.S.C. 1342">
  <data key="d0">31 U.S.C. 1342</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">This U.S. Code section prohibits acceptance of voluntary services, referenced in the Limitation of Government's Obligation clause.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-516b1e6efecfd543f141d1e1135ec455</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="L.10 Contractor Use of Mandatory Sources of Supply">
  <data key="d0">L.10 Contractor Use of Mandatory Sources of Supply</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">L.10 Contractor Use of Mandatory Sources of Supply outlines requirements for obtaining specific supplies from nonprofit agencies under FAR Clause 52.208-9.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR Clause 52.208-9">
  <data key="d0">FAR Clause 52.208-9</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR Clause 52.208-9 mandates that certain supplies be obtained from nonprofit agencies participating in the Committee program under 41 U.S.C. 8504.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Committee for the Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled">
  <data key="d0">Committee for the Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Committee for the Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled operates the program requiring certain supplies from nonprofit agencies under 41 U.S.C. 8504.&lt;SEP&gt;The Committee for the Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled operates a program under 41 U.S.C. 8504 for supplying items to government contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Logistics Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Logistics Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Defense Logistics Agency provides supplies such as trash liners, toilet paper, paper towels, hand soap, and hand sanitizer for government use.&lt;SEP&gt;The Defense Logistics Agency operates the FedMall application as indicated in the supplier registration website.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="General Services Administration">
  <data key="d0">General Services Administration</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The General Services Administration offers supplies including trash liners, toilet paper, paper towels, hand soap, and hand sanitizer available for government contracts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Department of Veterans Affairs">
  <data key="d0">Department of Veterans Affairs</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Department of Veterans Affairs supplies items like trash liners, toilet paper, paper towels, hand soap, and hand sanitizer for government procurement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Trash Liners">
  <data key="d0">Trash Liners</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Trash liners are mandatory supplies required to be obtained from nonprofit agencies for use by the Government under this contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Trash Liners are mandatory supplies required to be obtained from nonprofit agencies for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Toilet Paper">
  <data key="d0">Toilet Paper</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Toilet paper is a required supply to be sourced from nonprofit agencies participating in the Committee program for government use.&lt;SEP&gt;Toilet Paper is a mandatory supply required to be obtained from nonprofit agencies for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Paper Towels">
  <data key="d0">Paper Towels</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Paper towels must be procured from the Committee program's nonprofit agencies as per legal requirements for this contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Paper Towels are mandatory supplies required to be obtained from nonprofit agencies for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Hand Soap">
  <data key="d0">Hand Soap</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Hand soap is listed as a mandatory supply available from DLA, GSA, or VA for government contract fulfillment.&lt;SEP&gt;Hand Soap is a mandatory supply required to be obtained from nonprofit agencies for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790154</data>
</node>
<node id="Hand Sanitizer">
  <data key="d0">Hand Sanitizer</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Hand sanitizer is a required item to be obtained through mandatory sources for use in the contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Hand Sanitizer is a mandatory supply required to be obtained from nonprofit agencies for the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="L.11 All or None Offers">
  <data key="d0">L.11 All or None Offers</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">L.11 All or None Offers modifies FAR 52.215-1 to require offers for all line items, with failure leading to rejection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.215-1">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.215-1</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.215-1 provides instructions to offerors for competitive acquisition, modified in this solicitation for all or none basis.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR 52.215-1 is a provision referenced for late submissions in negotiated solicitations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="L.12 Site Visit Instructions">
  <data key="d0">L.12 Site Visit Instructions</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">L.12 Site Visit Instructions details the scheduling, procedures, and requirements for a site visit tentatively set for 23-25 September 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Site Visit">
  <data key="d0">Site Visit</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Site Visit is scheduled for 23-25 September 2025 at NAS Jacksonville with itinerary in Attachment JL-3.&lt;SEP&gt;The Site Visit is tentatively scheduled for 23-25 September 2025, with government-provided transportation and specific security protocols.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-3">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-3</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-3 is the itinerary for the site visit.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JL-3 contains the itinerary for the site visit, including times and locations for departure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-4">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-4</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-4 is the Access Management System (AMAG) form required for site visit access.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-5">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-5</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-5 is the Blount Island Base Access Form needed for participants to gain entry during the site visit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Courtney Peterson">
  <data key="d0">Courtney Peterson</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Courtney Peterson is a Government point of contact for receiving PPQs via email at courtney.j.peterson3.civ@us.navy.mil.&lt;SEP&gt;Courtney Peterson is the Contract Specialist handling pre-award inquiries for the solicitation.&lt;SEP&gt;Courtney Peterson is a contact for submitting required forms for the site visit, reachable at courtney.j.peterson3.civ@us.navy.mil.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Cari Fiebach">
  <data key="d0">Cari Fiebach</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Cari Fiebach is a Government point of contact for receiving PPQs via email at cari.l.fiebach.civ@us.navy.mil.&lt;SEP&gt;Cari Fiebach is a contact email for site visit form submissions, at cari.l.fiebach.civ@us.navy.mil.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-7">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-7</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-7 provides site visit directions for participants.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-8">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-8</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-8 includes site visit routes and serves as the template for the Small Business Subcontracting Plan.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="NS Mayport">
  <data key="d0">NS Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">NS Mayport is a naval station where security decisions for base access during the site visit are determined.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="L.13 Content of Proposals">
  <data key="d0">L.13 Content of Proposals</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">L.13 Content of Proposals specifies requirements for submitting responsibility determination, price proposal, and non-price proposal in separate volumes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Responsibility Determination Binder">
  <data key="d0">Responsibility Determination Binder</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Responsibility Determination Binder requires 2 copies including SF-33, amendments, team details, representations, financial statements, and other items for offeror responsibility assessment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Standard Form 33">
  <data key="d0">Standard Form 33</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Standard Form 33 is the prescribed form for solicitation, offer, and award under GSA-FAR 48 CFR 53.214(c), used for sealed bid or negotiated solicitations.&lt;SEP&gt;Standard Form 33 must be completed and signed with UEI number and CAGE code for the offeror or joint venture.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Unique Entity Identifier">
  <data key="d0">Unique Entity Identifier</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Unique Entity Identifier (UEI) is required on SF-33 and for identifying team members in proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="CAGE Code">
  <data key="d0">CAGE Code</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The CAGE Code is needed for all team members identified in responsibility and price proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="VETS-4212">
  <data key="d0">VETS-4212</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">VETS-4212 requires confirmation of the most recent filing or exemption explanation in the responsibility determination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Price Proposal Binder">
  <data key="d0">Price Proposal Binder</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Price Proposal Binder requires 2 copies including team details, pricing data, and electronic submissions on CD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Non-Price Proposal Binder">
  <data key="d0">Non-Price Proposal Binder</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Non-Price Proposal Binder requires 3 copies with factor requirements, limited to 150 pages, and electronic format on CD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment J-0200000-17 Exhibit Line Item Numbers">
  <data key="d0">Attachment J-0200000-17 Exhibit Line Item Numbers</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment J-0200000-17 Exhibit Line Item Numbers is used for submitting ELIN pricing data in spreadsheet format.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="L.14 Small Business Subcontracting Plan">
  <data key="d0">L.14 Small Business Subcontracting Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">L.14 Small Business Subcontracting Plan requires other than small businesses to submit a plan using Attachment JL-8 template per FAR 19.7.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Subcontracting Plan">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Subcontracting Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">The Small Business Subcontracting Plan must include goals consistent with small business participation and is reviewed for acceptability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="NAVFAC">
  <data key="d0">NAVFAC</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">NAVFAC is the Naval Facilities Engineering Systems Command responsible for setting command-wide small business subcontracting targets based on a percentage of total planned subcontract dollars.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC sets command-wide small business subcontracting targets including 40% for Small Business and others.&lt;SEP&gt;NAVFAC is the organization responsible for the Contractor Incident Reporting System used in safety evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business">
  <data key="d0">Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Small Business is targeted at 40% of total planned subcontract dollars in the subcontracting plan.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="HUBZone Small Business">
  <data key="d0">HUBZone Small Business</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">HUBZone Small Business has a 3% target in the small business subcontracting plan.&lt;SEP&gt;A category of small business concerns located in historically underutilized business zones for participation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.204-7">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.204-7</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.204-7 addresses System for Award Management requirements effective November 2024.&lt;SEP&gt;FAR 52.204-7 is the System for Award Management provision that triggers applicability of other representations like FAR 52.223-22.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.204-16">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.204-16</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.204-16 covers Commercial and Government Entity Code Reporting effective August 2020.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.204-22">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.204-22</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.204-22 pertains to Alternative Line Item Proposal effective January 2017.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS 252.237-7024">
  <data key="d0">DFARS 252.237-7024</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 252.237-7024 requires offerors to submit a plan for the notice of continuation of essential contractor services effective October 2010 as part of the responsibility determination.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-1">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-1</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">A Microsoft Excel attachment for basis of estimate on staffing levels for the total effort including prime and subcontractors.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JL-1 is a Microsoft Excel spreadsheet for submitting staffing levels, labor hours, and basis of estimate for each specification item.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JL-1 is submitted in hard copy and Excel format on CD as part of the non-price proposal requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JL-2">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JL-2</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JL-2 is the Government Preaward Inquiry Form for submitting inquiries.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JL-2 is the Government Pre-Award Inquiry form used for submitting written questions in accordance with Section L.4.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Section L.4">
  <data key="d0">Section L.4</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section L.4 provides the Pre-Award Inquiry Form for submitting questions related to the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Performance Work Statement">
  <data key="d0">Performance Work Statement</data>
  <data key="d1">statement_of_work</data>
  <data key="d2">Performance Work Statement outlines the requirements for recurring Base Operations Support Services and applicable attachments.&lt;SEP&gt;Performance Work Statement outlines the requirements for base operations support services, including labor, supervision, management, tools, materials, equipment, and other necessary items for recurring and non-recurring work.&lt;SEP&gt;The Performance Work Statement defines the scope of services for relevant projects in corporate experience and past performance evaluations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Performance Work Statement includes performance objectives that offerors must demonstrate understanding of rather than merely restating in proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e097b0647fa14f34c4ff76380ed4beb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790155</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Participation Commitment Document">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Participation Commitment Document</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">The Small Business Participation Commitment Document (SBPCD) specifies participation requirements as percentages of the total contract value for small businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 19.7">
  <data key="d0">FAR 19.7</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 19.7 governs the requirements for small business subcontracting plans for other than small businesses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Small Business Utilization and Participation Factor">
  <data key="d0">Small Business Utilization and Participation Factor</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">The Small Business Utilization and Participation Factor requires the SBSP to be consistent with commitments offered in proposals and lists small businesses considered in evaluations.&lt;SEP&gt;The Small Business Utilization and Participation Factor assesses commitments offered in proposals for small business utilization, detailed in Attachment JM-2.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JM-2">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JM-2</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">An attachment for demonstrating historical small business utilization for projects under Factor 1.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JM-2 is referenced in the Small Business Utilization and Participation factor for commitments offered in proposals.&lt;SEP&gt;Attachment JM-2 details the Small Business Utilization and Participation Factor for evaluation in proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Section B">
  <data key="d0">Section B</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section B details supplies or services and prices or costs, including 27 contract line item numbers structured for base and option periods, pricing of CLINs supported by exhibit line item numbers, maximum NTE and minimum guarantee, unit price adjustments, and specific CLIN descriptions for recurring and non-recurring work.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains pre-priced line item services supported by Section J ELINs, requiring catalog upload to FedMall and tracking of ordered quantities.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains pricing information submitted within the proposal for evaluation of inconsistencies.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains the pricing schedule and requires completion for solicitation submittal.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B of the contract supports GCPC orders for supplies and services.&lt;SEP&gt;Section B contains line item numbers and details used in the pricing spreadsheet data submission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f8cbd3bc2ef4445a2ce77064100a7a3e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Section J">
  <data key="d0">Section J</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section J provides ELINs supporting the pre-priced line items in Section B for ordering via FedMall.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J includes the Exhibit Line Item Number (ELIN) Pricing Attachment with multiple worksheets for pricing submission.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J of the contract provides ELINs supporting Section B for GCPC orders.&lt;SEP&gt;Section J includes attachments such as J-0200000-17 for Exhibit Line Item Numbers in pricing proposals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="ELIN">
  <data key="d0">ELIN</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">ELINs are Equipment Line Item Numbers available for ordering via FedMall, including specific items like Temporary HVAC units and services, applicable across all periods of performance.&lt;SEP&gt;ELIN refers to Exhibit Line Item Numbers used for pricing allocation and evaluation in the proposal submission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Price Evaluation Factor">
  <data key="d0">Price Evaluation Factor</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">The Price Evaluation Factor evaluates proposals for unbalanced pricing and appropriate allocation based on customer solicitation requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6266f048b10bdb8222f03b8f5e597d7e</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Systems Approach">
  <data key="d0">Systems Approach</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">A systems approach maintains functioning systems including all mechanically and electrically interlocked ancillary parts, equipment, and components without listing every part.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Fire Protection System">
  <data key="d0">Fire Protection System</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">A functioning system requiring maintenance of all interlocked parts as part of the systems approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="HVAC System">
  <data key="d0">HVAC System</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">A functioning system requiring maintenance of all interlocked parts as part of the systems approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Utility Systems">
  <data key="d0">Utility Systems</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Functioning systems such as fire protection and HVAC that require comprehensive maintenance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Limits of Liability (LOL)">
  <data key="d0">Limits of Liability (LOL)</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Limits specified in multiple annexes, sub-annexes, and spec items that must be understood and applied.&lt;SEP&gt;Limits of Liability (LOL) are contractual clauses applied across multiple annexes and specification items, requiring understanding and application by the offeror.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Supply Chain Management">
  <data key="d0">Supply Chain Management</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Management necessary to ensure materials, supplies, and equipment availability meet contractual delivery timelines.&lt;SEP&gt;Supply Chain Management is necessary to ensure timely availability of materials, supplies, and equipment to meet contractual delivery timelines in the performance work statement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
<node id="Unit Price Labor (UPL)">
  <data key="d0">Unit Price Labor (UPL)</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">A rate for performing one hour of work-in-place for work over Limits of Liability and other over-and-above work, encompassing all applicable costs including subcontracted work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b1019473eb9ce96e37dbd7a39cfdf02d</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790156</data>
</node>
