<node id="Section G - Contract Administration Data">
  <data key="d0">Section G - Contract Administration Data</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section G - Contract Administration Data outlines contract administration assignment to NAVFAC Southeast PWD Mayport, COR appointment, blanket task orders, performance assessment, and payment instructions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Contracting Officer'S Representative">
  <data key="d0">Contracting Officer'S Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contracting Officer's Representative is appointed to assist in contract administration, providing instructions on limitations, deadlines, and responsible for inspection and acceptance of deliverables, with name, address, and email TBD.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Blanket Task Order">
  <data key="d0">Blanket Task Order</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Blanket Task Order is a mechanism reserved by the Government for issuing bulk funding for non-recurring work, requiring Contracting Officer authorization before performance commences, including firm fixed-price not-to-exceed amounts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Dfars 252.201-7000 Contracting Officer'S Representative">
  <data key="d0">Dfars 252.201-7000 Contracting Officer'S Representative</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 252.201-7000 Contracting Officer's Representative is a clause incorporated by reference with effective date Dec 1991.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Dfars 252.232-7003 Electronic Submission Of Payment Requests And Receiving Reports">
  <data key="d0">Dfars 252.232-7003 Electronic Submission Of Payment Requests And Receiving Reports</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 252.232-7003 Electronic Submission of Payment Requests and Receiving Reports is a clause incorporated by reference with effective date Dec 2018.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Dfars 252.232-7006 Wide Area Workflow Payment Instructions">
  <data key="d0">Dfars 252.232-7006 Wide Area Workflow Payment Instructions</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 252.232-7006 Wide Area WorkFlow Payment Instructions is a clause incorporated by full text effective Jan 2023, detailing electronic invoicing procedures, WAWF access, training, submission methods, and routing data.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Wide Area Workflow">
  <data key="d0">Wide Area Workflow</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Wide Area WorkFlow is the system for electronically processing vendor payment requests and receiving reports, requiring contractor registration and use of specific document types and routing data such as DoDAAC N68732, N69450, N46134.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Section H - Special Contract Requirements">
  <data key="d0">Section H - Special Contract Requirements</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section H - Special Contract Requirements includes provisions for protecting historical and archaeological resources and requirements for FedMall registration and processing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Historical And Archaeological Resources">
  <data key="d0">Historical And Archaeological Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical and archaeological resources must be protected in-place, reported immediately to the Contracting Officer, with work stopped in the discovery area until directed to resume, and Government retains ownership and control.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790158</data>
</node>
<node id="Fedmall">
  <data key="d0">Fedmall</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">FedMall is a U.S. Government-owned web-based ordering system for DOD and Federal activities to search and order goods and services, requiring contractor registration, catalog upload, and acceptance of electronic IQ orders via 128-bit encrypted email using PGP software or comparable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5874f638e9cb9ecd09e53d314b07e103</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
