  <data key="d0">Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement (DFARS)</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Federal Acquisition Regulation Supplement (DFARS) supplements the FAR for Department of Defense acquisitions, referenced in clauses.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Independent Government Estimate (IGE)">
  <data key="d0">Independent Government Estimate (IGE)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Independent Government Estimate (IGE) is used as a comparison technique to evaluate proposed prices for reasonableness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Line Item Number (CLIN)">
  <data key="d0">Contract Line Item Number (CLIN)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract Line Item Number (CLIN) is part of the pricing structure where totals are recomputed in case of discrepancies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Exhibit Line Item Number (ELIN)">
  <data key="d0">Exhibit Line Item Number (ELIN)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Exhibit Line Item Number (ELIN) unit prices must be rounded to two decimal places, with extended totals calculated accordingly for evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="PO Box 30 NAS Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">PO Box 30 NAS Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">PO Box 30 NAS Jacksonville is the mailing address component for serving protests to the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-9775b66c35e6cfe40c05dbf72803d6cd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Safety Management System">
  <data key="d0">Safety Management System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Safety Management System is a framework including management/leadership involvement, employee involvement, hazard prevention, hazard control, worksite analysis, and safety training, benchmarked against standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Technical Approach to Safety">
  <data key="d0">Technical Approach to Safety</data>
  <data key="d1">submission_instruction</data>
  <data key="d2">Technical Approach to Safety is a narrative submission limited to two single-sided pages describing SMS implementation, subcontractor selection, oversight processes, and safety compliance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="OSHA">
  <data key="d0">OSHA</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">OSHA is a source of public data reviewed by the Government for safety information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Incident Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Incident Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Incident Reporting System is NAVFAC's system for reporting incidents, used as a Government internal source for safety evaluation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Contractor Performance Assessment Reporting System is a database for past performance evaluations, required for submission if available for projects under Factor 1.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Contract Management System">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Contract Management System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Contract Management System is a Government internal source for contract information reviewed in safety evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance is evaluated based on recency, relevancy, and quality of recent projects, using CPARS, PPQ, and other sources to assess trends in task completion, deliverables, cooperation, and similarity to the current contract.&lt;SEP&gt;Past Performance is a non-cost/price factor evaluated based on the relevancy definition for projects demonstrating capability in similar services.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Past Performance Questionnaire">
  <data key="d0">Past Performance Questionnaire</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Past Performance Questionnaire is a form provided in the solicitation for clients to complete if CPARS is unavailable, to be submitted with the proposal or directly to Government contacts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System">
  <data key="d0">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Federal Awardee Performance and Integrity Information System is a database used by the Government to obtain past performance information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Electronic Subcontract Reporting System">
  <data key="d0">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Electronic Subcontract Reporting System is a database for subcontract information reviewed in past performance evaluations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv)">
  <data key="d0">FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv)</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 15.305(a)(2)(iv) is a Federal Acquisition Regulation clause applied when an offeror has no relevant past performance record, assigning a neutral confidence rating.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
