  <data key="d0">52.217-5 Evaluation of Options</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">52.217-5 Evaluation of Options is a FAR clause incorporated by reference with effective date July 1990 for evaluating contract options.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="N69450-25-R-0003">
  <data key="d0">N69450-25-R-0003</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N69450-25-R-0003 is the solicitation document containing sections on safety and past performance evaluations across pages 68 to 71.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Corporate Experience">
  <data key="d0">Corporate Experience</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Corporate Experience is Factor 1 of the solicitation, referenced for identifying projects to support past performance submissions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Subcontractors">
  <data key="d0">Subcontractors</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Subcontractors are entities selected by the offeror through an evaluation process and overseen for safety compliance during contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment D">
  <data key="d0">Attachment D</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment D is the first page of the Past Performance Questionnaire, to be completed and submitted with contract and client information if a full PPQ is unavailable.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Defense Contract Management Agency">
  <data key="d0">Defense Contract Management Agency</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Defense Contract Management Agency is a government agency from which past performance information is obtained, including through interviews with program managers, contracting officers, and fee determining officials.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6277b393cb9cf1d4f0f247c35b0fffa1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Mayport is a location in Florida, United States, serving as the site for inspection and acceptance and place of performance.&lt;SEP&gt;Mayport is the site associated with the BOS project in Solicitation N6945025R0003.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville is a location in Florida where work under the solicitation is to be performed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville">
  <data key="d0">Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville is a location in Florida where work under the solicitation is to be performed, along with outlying areas supported by these commands.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Inspector of Record PWD Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Inspector of Record PWD Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Inspector of Record PWD Mayport is the point of contact for inspection and acceptance, reachable at telephone 904-270-6716.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Contract Term">
  <data key="d0">Contract Term</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Contract Term starts on 01 January 2027 for one year initially, extendable to eight years with seven one-year option periods, and potentially further under FAR 52.217-8 and FAR 52.217-9.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Transition Period">
  <data key="d0">Transition Period</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Transition Period allows 90 days for mobilization after award by 30 September 2026 and 90 days prior to contract completion for demobilization to support the follow-on contractor.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Pre-Performance Conference">
  <data key="d0">Pre-Performance Conference</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Pre-Performance Conference occurs within 30 days of contract award to discuss scheduling and administration with the Contracting Officer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Deliverables">
  <data key="d0">Deliverables</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Deliverables are files from Section F provided as attachment N6945025R0003_SectionF.pdf on SAM website, submitted electronically in Microsoft Office 365 compatible format via email or CD-ROM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Option Line Items">
  <data key="d0">Option Line Items</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Option Line Items such as 0007 through 0027 specify inspection and acceptance locations and delivery periods from 2027 to 2031 at the place of performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Delivery Schedule">
  <data key="d0">Delivery Schedule</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Delivery Schedule outlines periods for line items 0001 through 0014 and options, each for one each at the place of performance starting from 01 January 2027.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-9">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-9</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-9 is the clause for Option to Extend the Term of the Contract, which the Government may use to extend the contract term in accordance with its provisions incorporated into the resulting contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Far 52.217-8">
  <data key="d0">Far 52.217-8</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">Far 52.217-8 is the clause for Option to Extend Services, providing regulatory authority to extend contract performance up to an additional six months beyond the established 96 months.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="Sam.gov">
  <data key="d0">Sam.gov</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Sam.gov is the website where the attachment N6945025R0003_SectionF.pdf for Section F files is posted.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790160</data>
</node>
<node id="N6945025R0003 Sectionf.pdf">
  <data key="d0">N6945025R0003 Sectionf.pdf</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">N6945025R0003_SectionF.pdf is the attachment file containing the files for Section F, accessible on the SAM website.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Florida">
  <data key="d0">Florida</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Florida is the state in the United States where Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville and Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville are located for contract performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Mcsf-Bi">
  <data key="d0">Mcsf-Bi</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Mcsf-Bi is the abbreviation for Marine Corps Support Facility - Blount Island Jacksonville, a performance location for the contract work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Navsta Mayport">
  <data key="d0">Navsta Mayport</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Navsta Mayport is the abbreviation for Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville, a primary location for work performance as specified in Section C.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Inspection And Acceptance Location">
  <data key="d0">Inspection And Acceptance Location</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Inspection And Acceptance Location is specified as Both at Destination for multiple option line items, with instructions referring to Section F and details for NAVFAC Southeast PWD Mayport.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Place Of Performance">
  <data key="d0">Place Of Performance</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Place Of Performance is designated as the sites including Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville, Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville, and outlying areas for deliveries under the contract.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Outlying Areas">
  <data key="d0">Outlying Areas</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Outlying Areas are the regions supported by Naval Station Mayport Jacksonville and Marine Corps Support Facility Blount Island Jacksonville, included in the scope of work performance locations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-729293c3f8703afb2cb5e31cb6ff90dd</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="WAWF">
  <data key="d0">WAWF</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">WAWF is a system accessed through the contracting activity's point of contact for invoicing purposes, with helpdesk support available at 866-618-5988.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Historical and Archaeological Resources">
  <data key="d0">Historical and Archaeological Resources</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Historical and archaeological resources encompass items and human skeletal remains discovered during work, requiring immediate protection, reporting to the Contracting Officer, and work stoppage until directed otherwise, with ownership retained by the Government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FEDMALL">
  <data key="d0">FEDMALL</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">FEDMALL is a U.S. Government-owned web-based ordering system enabling Department of Defense and Federal activities to search for and order goods and services, requiring contractor registration, catalog upload, and acceptance of electronic orders via encrypted email.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="PGP Personal Software">
  <data key="d0">PGP Personal Software</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">PGP Personal software, or a comparable solution, is required for the contractor to decrypt 128-bit encrypted order notification emails from FedMall.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="External Certification Authority">
  <data key="d0">External Certification Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The External Certification Authority program issues DoD-approved certificates to contractors for secure communication and authentication to DoD Information Systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
