  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-18">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-18</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.216-18, Ordering, authorizes issuance of delivery or task orders orally, by facsimile, or by electronic commerce methods.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.216-19">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.216-19</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.216-19, Order Limitations, is incorporated but not applicable to recurring work, FedMall orders, or the Governmentwide Commercial Purchase Card program.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Construction Work">
  <data key="d0">Construction Work</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Construction work under the contract includes major repair, minor construction, stand-alone demolition, and efforts under Non-Recurring ELINs, subject to specific labor standards clauses and wage rate requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.211-12">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.211-12</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.211-12, Liquidated Damages - Construction, applies to all construction work performed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.222-6">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.222-6</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.222-6, Construction Wage Rate Requirements, applies to all construction work performed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Miller Act">
  <data key="d0">Miller Act</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">The Miller Act governs performance and payment bond requirements incorporated into construction task orders.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="DFARS 211.106">
  <data key="d0">DFARS 211.106</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">DFARS 211.106 requires contractors to furnish and display identification for employees distinguishing them as contractor personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.246-4">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.246-4</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.246-4, Inspection of Services - Fixed-Price, serves as the basis for deductions and assessment of contractor performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Government Property">
  <data key="d0">Government Property</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Government property is not included in the contract, but Government-owned facilities, equipment, and utilities are made available in as-is condition for contract-related use only.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Key Personnel">
  <data key="d0">Key Personnel</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Key personnel are identified in Section C, with substitutions requiring Contracting Officer approval and comparable qualifications, without price changes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Consequences of Contractor's Failure to Perform">
  <data key="d0">Consequences of Contractor's Failure to Perform</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Consequences include re-performance, payment withholding, price reduction, liquidated damages assessment, and potential termination for unsatisfactory or non-performed work.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="Watchstanding Services">
  <data key="d0">Watchstanding Services</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Watchstanding services require qualified personnel, with penalties for unmanned posts including payment withholding and liquidated damages if failures occur.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.202-1">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.202-1</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 52.202-1, Definitions, is incorporated by reference effective June 2020.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3b65cbb31e854658ff984a34247acde1</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790161</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 52.203-13">
  <data key="d0">FAR 52.203-13</data>
  <data key="d1">clause</data>
