  <data key="d2">Period of Acceptance is 180 calendar days from the date specified for receipt of offers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bcb91b404a9ca74c18944c1ba7f80a2</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="IGE">
  <data key="d0">IGE</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">IGE refers to the Independent Government Estimate used in comparing proposed prices with historical information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="FAR 15.404-1">
  <data key="d0">FAR 15.404-1</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">FAR 15.404-1 is the Federal Acquisition Regulation clause guiding price analysis methodologies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="Section J ELIN Attachment">
  <data key="d0">Section J ELIN Attachment</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section J ELIN Attachment provides details for evaluating proposal pricing and correcting discrepancies.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="Section M.3">
  <data key="d0">Section M.3</data>
  <data key="d1">section</data>
  <data key="d2">Section M.3 outlines procedures for correcting discrepancies in proposals through clarifications or discussions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="Base Operations Support (BOS) Services">
  <data key="d0">Base Operations Support (BOS) Services</data>
  <data key="d1">statement_of_work</data>
  <data key="d2">Base Operations Support (BOS) Services encompass at least three specified annexes and one additional technical annex, excluding general information and management administration.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="Port Operations (0600000)">
  <data key="d0">Port Operations (0600000)</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Port Operations (0600000) is an annex similar to the RFP requirements for demonstrating relevant project experience.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="Facility Investment (1502000)">
  <data key="d0">Facility Investment (1502000)</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Facility Investment (1502000) includes completion of service orders, HVAC systems maintenance and repairs, fire protection systems maintenance and repairs, and two other facility investment spec items.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790163</data>
</node>
<node id="Electrical (1602000)">
  <data key="d0">Electrical (1602000)</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Electrical (1602000) covers transmission and distribution operations, maintenance, and repairs similar to RFP requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Water (1606000)">
  <data key="d0">Water (1606000)</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Water (1606000) includes raw water supply, water treatment plant and distribution system operation, laboratory and testing processes, maintenance, and repairs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="BSVE (1700000)">
  <data key="d0">BSVE (1700000)</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">BSVE (1700000) involves operations, maintenance, and repair of Civil Engineering Support Equipment (CESE) and Weight Handling Equipment (WHE) similar to RFP requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="RFP">
  <data key="d0">RFP</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">RFP is the Request for Proposal describing performance work statement, specifications, and evaluation criteria.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Attachment JM-1">
  <data key="d0">Attachment JM-1</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Attachment JM-1 provides space for narrative, organization chart, and teaming agreement for corporate affiliate experience.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Joint Venture (JV)">
  <data key="d0">Joint Venture (JV)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Joint Venture (JV) is a partnership where experience from JV entities or partners is submitted, limited to five projects total, with requirements for demonstrating portions of work performed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Mentor-Protege Agreements">
  <data key="d0">Mentor-Protege Agreements</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Mentor-Protege Agreements are approvals by the Small Business Administration allowing exceptions for JV experience submissions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 1">
  <data key="d0">Factor 1</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 1 evaluates Corporate Experience based on submission of two to five recent relevant projects demonstrating capability to meet solicitation requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Factor 2">
  <data key="d0">Factor 2</data>
  <data key="d1">evaluation_factor</data>
  <data key="d2">Factor 2 evaluates Management Approach, including workforce management, quality management system, scheduling, and phase-in plans, limited to 20 pages.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Quality Management System (QMS)">
  <data key="d0">Quality Management System (QMS)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Quality Management System (QMS) is a program ensuring compliance with management and administration requirements, performance objectives, and standards.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Phase-In Plan">
  <data key="d0">Phase-In Plan</data>
  <data key="d1">requirement</data>
  <data key="d2">Phase-In Plan ensures personnel, materials, and equipment are on site within 90 calendar days, including schedules, personnel actions, and acquisition details.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 6">
  <data key="d0">Annex 6</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 6 covers Port Operations as part of the technical approach requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 15">
  <data key="d0">Annex 15</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 15 covers Facilities Support, including sub-annexes for facility management, investment, custodial, pest control, waste management, training pools, and grounds maintenance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 16">
  <data key="d0">Annex 16</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 16 covers Utilities, including utilities management, electrical, and water sub-annexes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 17">
  <data key="d0">Annex 17</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 17 covers Transportation as part of the technical approach.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Annex 18">
  <data key="d0">Annex 18</data>
  <data key="d1">annex</data>
  <data key="d2">Annex 18 covers Environmental, with sub-annexes for NAVSTA and MCSF-BI.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Price Proposal">
  <data key="d0">Price Proposal</data>
  <data key="d1">submission_instruction</data>
  <data key="d2">Price Proposal is submitted by offerors and evaluated for reasonableness using historical information, market surveys, and other methodologies, including checks for unbalanced and inconsistent pricing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Offeror">
  <data key="d0">Offeror</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Offeror is the proposer required to submit corporate experience projects, management approaches, technical methodologies, and other required documentation in response to the solicitation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Unbalanced Pricing">
  <data key="d0">Unbalanced Pricing</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Unbalanced Pricing refers to situations where proposed prices are materially overstated or understated at line item levels, potentially representing unacceptable risk to the government despite an acceptable total price.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Corporate Affiliates">
  <data key="d0">Corporate Affiliates</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Corporate Affiliates include subsidiaries, sister companies, predecessor companies, and parent companies whose experience can be used by the offeror to demonstrate relevant projects, subject to submission of narratives, organization charts, and teaming agreements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Organization Chart">
  <data key="d0">Organization Chart</data>
  <data key="d1">deliverable</data>
  <data key="d2">Organization Chart is a required submission demonstrating corporate relationships of affiliates and management structure for workforce and key personnel.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Teaming Agreement">
  <data key="d0">Teaming Agreement</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Teaming Agreement or Letter of Commitment is submitted to show meaningful participation of corporate affiliates in the project.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Civil Engineering Support Equipment (CESE)">
  <data key="d0">Civil Engineering Support Equipment (CESE)</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Civil Engineering Support Equipment (CESE) requires operations, maintenance, and repair as part of BSVE (1700000) similar to RFP requirements.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Weight Handling Equipment (WHE)">
  <data key="d0">Weight Handling Equipment (WHE)</data>
  <data key="d1">technology</data>
  <data key="d2">Weight Handling Equipment (WHE) is included in BSVE (1700000) for operations, maintenance, and repair similar to the RFP.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Preventive Maintenance (PM) Program">
  <data key="d0">Preventive Maintenance (PM) Program</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Preventive Maintenance (PM) Program is a required methodology for maintenance in multiple annexes and sub-annexes, evaluated for efficiency and effectiveness.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Integrated Maintenance Program (IMP)">
  <data key="d0">Integrated Maintenance Program (IMP)</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Integrated Maintenance Program (IMP) is implemented for recurring services and compliance in various annexes, with QC oversight ensuring contractual obligations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="RS Means Facilities Maintenance &amp; Repair Cost Data">
  <data key="d0">RS Means Facilities Maintenance &amp; Repair Cost Data</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">RS Means Facilities Maintenance &amp; Repair Cost Data is an estimate data source used in the Basis of Estimate for labor hours and costs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ac133babc8ecde7c6f7014a40f53ce13</data>
  <data key="d4">_N6945025R0003.pdf</data>
  <data key="d5">1759790164</data>
</node>
<node id="Whitestone Building and Repair Cost Reference">
  <data key="d0">Whitestone Building and Repair Cost Reference</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
